<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11134g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11134g">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11134g"> 134(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> never saw him in a / flaming green suit</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Elles chantaient, elles riaient avec moi, et puis elles se prenaient &agrave; verser des larmes en songeant que je serais br&ucirc;l&eacute;. Une nuit que les Muscogulges avaient plac&eacute; leur camp sur le bord d&apos;une for&ecirc;t, j&apos;&eacute;tais assis aupr&egrave;s du <i>feu de la guerre</i>, avec le chasseur commis &agrave; ma garde. Tout &agrave; coup j&apos;entendis le murmure d&apos;un v&ecirc;tement sur l&apos;herbe, et une femme &agrave; demi voil&eacute;e vint s&apos;asseoir &agrave; mes c&ocirc;t&eacute;s. <br><font color="green">[They sang, they laughed with me, and then they began to shed tears, thinking that I would be burned. One night that the Muscogulges had placed their camp on the edge of a forest, I was seated near the fire of the war, with the hunter committed to my care. Suddenly I heard the murmur of a garment on the grass, and a half-veiled woman came and sat by my side.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) I, <i>Atala</i> 37</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
